Titanic Decision Tree Model

# front-matter
rm(list = ls()) #clear the workspace

library(data.table)

library(tidymodels)  # for the tune package, along with the rest of tidymodels

# Helper packages
library(rpart.plot)  # for visualizing a decision tree
library(vip)         # for variable importance plots
titanic_train <- fread('/Users/malcolmzerbe/practice_r/titanic/project/volume/data/interim/titanic_train.csv')
titanic_test <- fread('/Users/malcolmzerbe/practice_r/titanic/project/volume/data/interim/titanic_test.csv')

titanic_train <- na.omit(titanic_train)
titanic_test <- na.omit(titanic_test)

titanic_train <- as_tibble(titanic_train)
class(titanic_train)

titanic_test <- as_tibble(titanic_test)
class(titanic_test)

titanic_train <- titanic_train %>%
  select(-PassengerId)
titanic_test <- titanic_test %>%
  select(-PassengerId)

titanic_train
titanic_test
titanic_train
tune_spec <- decision_tree(
                cost_complexity = tune(),
                tree_depth = tune(),
                min_n = tune()
              ) %>%
             set_engine("rpart") %>%
             set_mode("classification")

tune_spec
Decision Tree Model Specification (classification)

Main Arguments:
  cost_complexity = tune()
  tree_depth = tune()
  min_n = tune()

Computational engine: rpart 
tree_grid <- grid_regular(cost_complexity(),
                          tree_depth(),
                          min_n(),
                          levels = 1)

tree_grid
tree_grid %>%
  count(tree_depth)
set.seed(234)
titanic_folds <- vfold_cv(titanic_train)
titanic_folds
#  10-fold cross-validation 
set.seed(345)

tree_wf <- workflow() %>%
  add_model(tune_spec) %>%
  add_formula(Survived ~ .)

tree_res <-
  tree_wf %>%
  tune_grid(
      resamples = titanic_folds,
      grid = tree_grid,
      control = control_grid(save_pred = TRUE),
      metrics = metric_set(roc_auc)
      )

  tree_res %>%
  collect_predictions(parameters = best_tree) %>%
  roc_curve(diabetes, .pred_neg) %>%
  mutate(model = "Decision Tree")
